state management : Deciding whe to create piece of state, what types of  state are necessary, where to place each piece of state, and how data flows through the app 

Local State: state needed only by one or few components

state that is defined in a component and only that component and child components have access to it (by passinf via props)

Global State: state needed by many components across the app


shared state that is accessible to every component in the entire application


context API    Redux




when and where

